jQuery.click2play

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

jQuery plugin that converts video embeds in document into clickable thumbnails.

Released by Greg Leuch <http://gleuch.com>.
Originally for Rocketboom <http://rocketboom.com> & Know Your Meme <http://knowyourmeme.com>.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Easy to use:

  1. Add jquery.click2play.js to the page.
  2. Add the initalizer:
      $(document).ready(
        // Initializer

        // Options include skipFirst (true = leave first video as embed)
        // and facebox (true = open in jQuery.facebox)

        $('body').click2play(false, false);

      });
  3. Copy images from /images and styling from click2play.css into respective areas in your app.
  4. Load video-heavy page and click away!


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Upcoming Features

  - Condensing libraries into the jQuery function with $.extend();
  - Adding libraries for Hulu, Blip, Break, and others.
  - Adding ability to sniff for params with thumbnail url.


